repair.repairedDockerfile:
# Use the VG Docker image and build over it
FROM quay.io/vgteam/vg:v1.27.1

# Update Ubuntu Software repository
RUN apt-get update

# Upgrade Ubuntu Software repository
RUN apt-get upgrade -y

# make sure having gcc, make and git
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends build-essential -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends make -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends sudo -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends git -y

# Install curl
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends curl -y

# Build VG from source (static binaries no more available)
RUN sudo apt-get -y --no-install-recommends install build-essential git cmake pkg-config libncurses-dev libbz2-dev \
                     protobuf-compiler libprotoc-dev libprotobuf-dev libjansson-dev \
                     automake libtool jq bc rs curl unzip redland-utils \
                     librdf-dev bison flex gawk lzma-dev liblzma-dev liblz4-dev \
                     libffi-dev libcairo-dev

# Download and install python3.7
WORKDIR /grafimo_wd
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends python3.7 -y
RUN update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/python python /usr/bin/python3.7 50
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends python3-distutils -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends manpages-dev -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends python-dev -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends python3-dev -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends libpython3.7-dev -y

# Install GRAFIMO external dependencies
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends tabix -y
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends graphviz -y

# Making sure that pip is available
RUN curl -f https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py -o get-pip.py
RUN python get-pip.py
RUN apt-get install --no-install-recommends python3-pip -y
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir pandas
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir numpy
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir statsmodels
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir numba
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir Cython
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir setuptools
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir wheel
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir sphinx
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir -U colorama

# remove the pip installation file
RUN rm get-pip.py

# Download and build GRAFIMO
RUN pip3 install --no-cache-dir grafimo

# check we have GRAFIMO, vg, tabix and graphviz available and in PATH
RUN which grafimo && which vg && which tabix && which dot

# Set expose to port 80 and 443
EXPOSE 80 443
